{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 10.4.2 Benefits of Victory\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Just as when you experience {\b defeat} you can suffer ongoing ill effects in addition to the loss of the {\b prize} at hand, when you win you can gain benefits from that {\b victory}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A {\b benefit of victory} gives you a bonus on the selected {\b abilities}, or in the specified situation, as determined by your {\b victory} level.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A PC may apply {\b bonuses} from multiple {\b benefits} to a single {\b contest}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 From the least to the most robust the four {\b states of fortune} are: {\b fresh}, {\b pumped}, {\b invigorated}, and {\b heroic}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 10.4.2.1 Fresh\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you are {\b fresh}, you are lively and find it easier to succeed at {\b contests} related to your {\b victory}. You are on a roll and feel confident and able. Until you are {\b defeated}, you gain a +3 {\b bonus} to all related abilities.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You may be refreshed multiple times on the same {\b ability}. These are cumulative until {\b defeat} occurs.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Unless your GM has a dramatic reason to decide otherwise, your {\b freshness} vanishes at the end of a session, after one day of idleness, or when in-game events justify their removal.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 10.4.2.2 Pumped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you are {\b pumped}, you are energized, physically, socially, or emotionally, and you are much likelier to succeed when attempting similar actions in the future. You gain a +6 {\b bonus} to all related abilities. {\b Pumped} combines with {\b fresh} and {\b pumped}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As good as your condition may be, an extended period of idleness will cause you to lose your edge. A single {\b pumped} goes away after one week of idleness, or when an in-game event (like long drunken party) occurs to make their removal seem believable.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 10.4.2.3 Invigorated\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you are {\b invigorated}, you are pulsing with hormones, mentally focused, or exuding confidence. Physically you can push your body to new personal bests of achievement, socially confidant and exuding charisma, and emotionally you are in touch with your feelings and resonate with those of others. Although this will fade with time, you gain a +9 {\b bonus} to all related abilities. {\b Invigorated} combines with {\b pumped} and {\b fresh}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Being {\b invigorated} goes away after a month\u8217's idleness, or an in-game event, as above.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 10.4.2.4 Heroic\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you are {\b heroic}, you have become unstoppable, physically at peak performance, socially, everyone wants to be you or be with you, and emotionally you have gained new insights into yourself and others around you. Although this will fade with time, you gain a {\b bump} {\b bonus} to all related abilities. Being {\b heroic} combines with {\b invigorated}, {\b pumped} and {\b fresh}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Being {\b heroic} goes away after a season\u8217's idleness, or an in-game event, as above.\par}
